ObjectField.Name: PERTSTINTERVAL
ObjectField.ToolTip: - The interval between the periodic tests, specified in units of 100ms. A value of 0 in this field sets a default value of 2 to give a 200ms interval

ObjectField.Name: PERTSTHOLDOFF
ObjectField.ToolTip:
- Specifies how long a periodic test can be delayed by a higher priority operation, these are, typically, Detect Integration or calibration. The hold off delay is specified in ms.
A setting of 0 means no hold off delay while a value of 255 mans indefinite hold off.

ObjectField.Name: PERTSTRPTFACTOR
ObjectField.ToolTip: - Helps determine how often the result of the periodic test is reported. This is specified as a multiple of the periodic test interval (PERTSTINTERVAL). So a report occurs every Periodic Test Interval (PERTSTINTERVAL) x Periodic Test Report Factor (PERTSTRPTFACTOR). A setting of 1 will result in a report every periodic test interval (PERTSTINTERVAL).

ObjectField.Name: PERTSTRPTWIDTH
ObjectField.ToolTip:
- Specifies the periodic test report GPIO pulse width. The pulse width is specified in units of 1/256 or the periodic test report interval whichh is defined as Periodic Test Interval (PERTSTINTERVAL) x Periodic Test Report Factor (PERTSTRPTFACTOR). A valueof 0 is inerpreted as 256 which results in a steady state.
NOTE;- The GPIO configuration T19 trigger control must be configured (refer to T19 TRIGGER[] fields)
